Q: Create a service performance report showing service name, total patients admitted, and a performance category based on the following: 'Excellent' if avg satisfaction >= 85, 'Good' if >= 75, 'Fair' if >= 65, otherwise 'Needs Improvement'. Order by average satisfaction descending.

ğğ®ğğ«ğ²: SELECT service, SUM(patients_admitted) AS total_admitted, ROUND(AVG(patient_satisfaction), 2) AS avg_satisfaction,
 CASE
 WHEN AVG(patient_satisfaction) >= 85 THEN 'Excellent'
 WHEN AVG(patient_satisfaction) >= 75 THEN 'Good'
 WHEN AVG(patient_satisfaction) >= 65 THEN 'Fair'
 ELSE 'Needs Improvement'
 END AS performance_category
FROM services_weekly
GROUP BY service
ORDER BY avg_satisfaction DESC;
